<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1931-01-03T13:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1931-01-03T13:00:00-05:00" n="410" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d410">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">814.01/27: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Guatemala</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Guatemala</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-01-03T11:00:00-07:00">January 3, 1931—11
                                a.m.</date><lb/>[Received 2:55 p.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>5. German Minister authorized to recognize Reina Andrade but believe he
                            will take no action until I have received your instructions.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>